gobblin.cluster

Class GobblinHelixJobLauncher

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.runtime.AbstractJobLauncher
      • gobblin.cluster.GobblinHelixJobLauncher
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JobLauncher, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    @Alpha
public class GobblinHelixJobLauncher
extends AbstractJobLauncher
    An implementation of JobLauncher that launches a Gobblin job using the Helix task framework.

    This class uses the Helix task execution framework to run tasks of Gobblin jobs. It creates one Helix JobQueue per job and submits every scheduled runs of a job to its JobQueue, where Helix picks up them and submit them for execution. After submitting the job run to its JobQueue, it waits for the job to complete and collects the output TaskState(s) upon completion.

    Each WorkUnit of the job is persisted to the FileSystem of choice and the path to the file storing the serialized WorkUnit is passed to the Helix task running the WorkUnit as a user-defined property GobblinClusterConfigurationKeys.WORK_UNIT_FILE_PATH. Upon startup, the Helix task reads the property for the file path and de-serializes the WorkUnit from the file.

    This class runs in the GobblinClusterManager. The actual task execution happens in the in the GobblinTaskRunner.
